# Safe change policy

This app runs live flight operations. Default to conservative edits.

## Scope

- Fix only what the user asked for; no drive-by refactors
- Do not rename modules, routes, or global Angular module names
- Do not delete scheduled jobs or Socket.io handlers without understanding impact
- Do not run destructive git commands (`reset --hard`, `clean -fd`, force push)

## Database

- No `DROP`, `TRUNCATE`, or `sequelize.sync({ force: true })`
- Do not change Sequelize model schemas without a migration plan
- SQLite `dev.sqlite` is local only; production uses PostgreSQL

## Auth & roles

- Preserve existing role checks (`guest`, `user`, `admin`, `superadmin`)
- New endpoints must use `auth.isAuthenticated()` or `auth.hasRole(...)` consistently with sibling routes
- Do not weaken or bypass JWT validation

## Dependencies

- Do not add new npm/bower packages unless necessary
- Match existing code style: `'use strict'`, Babel imports on server, AngularJS DI arrays where used

## Commits

- Only commit when the user explicitly asks
